featured.text: The position of the bindi is standard: center of the forehead, close to the eyebrows.
he should have large ears, upward-slanting eyes and eyebrows.

definition.zh_def: 眉毛，位於眼睛上方的毛髮。
definition.en_def: The hair that grows above the eye, typically arching over the eye socket.
definition.example: She raised her eyebrow in surprise.
